cs.LO, cs.FL, cs.PL, cs.CL, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with formal language theory and learning algorithms, which are closely related to logic. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also a likely category as the paper specifically deals with nominal automata and regular languages. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as nominal automata are amenable to abstract modelling of resource-aware computations, which is a topic of interest in programming languages. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a possible category as the paper deals with regular expressions with binders, which are used in natural language processing. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper studies the theoretical complexity of the proposed learning algorithm.
